Modernized the service to SQLAlchemy 2-style session semantics without touching tests or seed/context files. In [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run1/workspace/app/repository.py:1), repository reads/counts now use `select(...)`, and `create_entry()` flushes instead of committing so callers keep transaction ownership. In [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run1/workspace/app/worker.py:4), each worker operation now runs inside a single `session_factory.begin()` block, so failures roll back intermediate `"processing"` updates. In [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run1/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:4), dry-run planning/reconcile paths intentionally trigger rollback while still returning their planned output.

I also updated the cutover guidance in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v3-dirty-state-run1/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1) to document the new boundary rules and the removal of helper-level commits.

Validation: `pytest -q tests/test_api.py tests/test_worker.py tests/test_admin_cli.py` passed (`3 passed`). The only remaining output was a non-blocking `PytestCacheWarning` about writing `.pytest_cache` outside the writable sandbox.
